                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(center)\"><placeName>New York</placeName>\n                <add>נאכט לברתות</add>\n                <date>Nov. 19. 1859</date>.</p>\n            <p><addressee>Rev. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>,\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">My dear Sir—</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">I have just received a letter from<lb/> my lawyer in\n                    <placeName>Charleston</placeName> summoning me home, in the<lb/> most emphatic\n                language, as my personal attendance at<lb/> the settlement of some worldy affair was\n                indispensably<lb/> necessary. I have, therefore, being very busy with\n                preparations<lb/> for my departure—only time to request you for the favor of<lb/>\n                telling me, <hi rend=\"underline\">by return of mail</hi>, <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >who</hi> sent you the correspond-<lb/>ence between myself and the committee\n                presenting me the<lb/> Testimonial of some of my former flock. The\n                cor-<lb/>respondence as published, but more so the accompanying<lb/> remarks make it\n                appear, as tho' the presentation was<lb/> made <hi rend=\"underline\">after</hi> I had\n                refused the request to remain. Just<lb/> the reverse took place. The Ladies\n                presented their gift on<lb/> the <date>18 of October</date>, the gentleman on the\n                    <date>21</date>, in the morning,<lb/> and my replies to them bear the same dates\n                respectively.<lb/> The petition—of which I <sic>sentt</sic> you a copy\n                    <sic>inclosed</sic> with<lb/> this—was presented to me on <date>Friday</date>\n                night, at the<lb/> Synagogue, after divine service, and answered by me on<lb/>\n                <date>Sunday the 23d</date>, <hi rend=\"underline\">a few hours before my departure\n                    for</hi><lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\"><placeName>New-York</placeName></hi>. I don't wish that you\n                should make any<lb/> public use of either this letter or the copy of the\n                petition<lb/> accompanying this; both are communicated to you to give<lb/> you some\n                intimation of the reason why I am anxious</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3862bx9w/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
